  "text": "Results are normalized to energy data obtained for conventional CMOS circuit evaluated under the operating condition of DD = 0.3 V, activity factor ( ) of 0.2, and clock cycle time ( clk ) of 80 FO4 (FO4 represents the delay of a CMOS inverter driving four identical inverters), which is typical of low power VLSI circuits [CITATION_1] . More precisely, Figure 7 plots OP considering clk = 80 FO4 for = 0.1, 0.2, and 0.3.",
